The paper deals with the detection of large-scale disruptions in the Internet routing system, which is a topic related to network security and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the analysis of data and the development of algorithms, which are topics related to computer science theory and algorithms, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely categories as well. The paper also proposes a method for early detection of routing anomalies, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the limitations and challenges of the proposed method, which is related to information theory and communication systems, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category as well.
